  	<itemizedlist>
  		<listitem><para>In tables, you can address the row of a table either by using its index or by
  		entering the value in the first column of the particular row.</para></listitem>
  		<listitem><para>The first row is 1 and so on.</para></listitem>
  		<listitem><para>The row of table headers at the top of the table can be addressed using the index
  		0.</para></listitem>
  		<listitem><para>If the cell you want to execute an action on is the fourth row and contains the
  		value <emphasis>Price</emphasis> in the first column, you can address the row either with
  		the index <emphasis>4</emphasis> or with the string <emphasis>Price</emphasis>.</para></listitem>
  	</itemizedlist>
  
  
